Scenarios:
1.Sign-In and Sign-Out:

Open the Amazon homepage.
Click on the "Sign-In" button.
Enter valid credentials (username and password) and click "Sign-In."
Verify that the user is successfully signed in.
Click on the account menu and select "Sign-Out."
Verify that the user is signed out and redirected to the homepage.

2. Search for a Product:

Open the Amazon homepage.
Enter a product name (e.g., "laptop") in the search bar.
Click on the search button.
Verify that the search results page is displayed.

3.Filter and Sort Search Results:

Search for a product as mentioned in scenario 1.
Apply specific filters (e.g., brand, price range, etc.).
Sort the search results by a particular criterion (e.g., price, customer ratings).
Verify that the results are correctly filtered and sorted.